            "content": {
                "raw": "This looks good to me. @ngoldbaum, i'd maybe try an even bigger default (16 pt). Honestly, fonts being too small is far more common than too large. Of course, we really need to figure out how to not have matplotlib use two different fonts on all plots (one for labels in \"latex\", one for tick marks and on-plot annotations), but that's way beyond the scope of this PR. For now, looks good.",
                "html": "<p>This looks good to me. <a href=\"/ngoldbaum/\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"@ngoldbaum\" class=\"mention\">Nathan Goldbaum</a>, i'd maybe try an even bigger default (16 pt). Honestly, fonts being too small is far more common than too large. Of course, we really need to figure out how to not have matplotlib use two different fonts on all plots (one for labels in \"latex\", one for tick marks and on-plot annotations), but that's way beyond the scope of this PR. For now, looks good.</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
